-- Children's Place April same-store sales up
-- 
-- Thu May 8, 2008 7:06am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/05/08/us-usa-retailsales-childrensplace-idUSN0833972320080508

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Children's Place Retail Stores Inc ( PLCE.O ) said on Thursday its sales at stores open at least a year rose a 15 percent in April. 

 Wall Street had been expected a same-store sales gain of 5.3 percent, according to Reuters Estimates. The children's clothing retailer said total sales rose 24 percent for the four weeks ended May 3 to $128.7 million. The company, which recently sold its Disney store chain to Walt Disney Co ( DIS.N ), said same-store sales for the quarter rose 5 percent. (Reporting by  Aarthi Sivaraman  and  Martinne Geller , editing by Mark Porter and  Derek Caney )